 [{"role": "author", "vocabulary": "crossref"}]}], "venue": "2024 International Conference on Distributed Systems, Computer Networks and Cybersecurity (ICDSCNC)", "container-title": ["2024 International Conference on Distributed Systems, Computer Networks and Cybersecurity (ICDSCNC)"], "abstract": null, "url": "https://doi.org/10.1109/icdscnc62492.2024.10939837", "URL": "https://doi.org/10.1109/icdscnc62492.2024.10939837", "year": 2024, "publication_year": 2024, "citation_count": 0, "_crossref_type": "proceedings-article"}]}, "_crossref_type": "proceedings-article"}, {"title": "Construction of Safety Early Warning Model for Construction of Engineering Based on Convolution Neural Network", "abstract": "<jats:p>In recent years, China’s engineering construction management level has been greatly improved, but compared with other industries, the construction industry still has low production efficiency, serious waste, and low level of information problems, and especially in the process of engineering management practice, schedule delay has become the focus of engineering management problems. With the continuous development of science and technology, computer and information technology have been continuously applied in engineering, among which deep neural network (DNN) technology, lean management", "url": "https://doi.org/10.1155/2022/8937084", "doi": "10.1155/2022/8937084", "arxiv_id": null, "source": "crossref", "hits": {"crossref": [{"title": "Construction of Safety Early Warning Model for Construction of Engineering Based on Convolution Neural Network", "doi": "10.1155/2022/8937084", "DOI": "10.1155/2022/8937084", "authors": ["Changge Zhao"], "author": [{"ORCID": "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0762-8426", "authenticated-orcid": true, "given": "Changge", "family": "Zhao", "sequence": "first", "affiliation": [{"name": "Henan University of Engineering, Henan, Zhengzhou 45000, China"}], "role": [{"role": "author", "vocabulary": "crossref"}]}], "venue": "Computational Intelligence and Neuroscience", "container-title": ["Computational Intelligence and Neuroscience"], "abstract": "<jats:p>In recent years, China’s engineering construction management level has been greatly improved, but compared with other industries, the construction industry still has low production efficiency, serious waste, and low level of information problems, and especially in the process of engineering management practice, schedule delay has become the focus of engineering management problems. With the continuous development of science and technology, computer and information technology have been continuously applied in engineering, among which deep neural network (DNN) technology, lean management, information visualization technology, and other technologies have become the hot spot of industry research, and the application of these emerging technologies to improve the level of project schedule control has become an urgent demand of the industry. Therefore, on the basis of deep learning, this paper analyzes the principle and application of object detection and feature extraction constructed by neural network and combines text feature extraction and image feature extraction methods. This application provides a new idea for the development of the construction industry.</jats:p>", "url": "https://doi.org/10.1155/2022/8937084", "URL": "https://doi.org/10.1155/2022/8937084", "year": 2022, "publication_year": 2022, "citation_count": 1, "_crossref_type": "journal-article"}]}, "_crossref_type": "journal-article"}, {"title": "Multi-Kernel Convolutional Neural Network-Transformer for Early Warning of Upset Events in Industrial Furnaces", "abstract": "", "url": "https://doi.org/10.2139/ssrn.5316635", "doi": "10.2139/ssrn.5316635", "arxiv_id": null, "source": "crossref", "hits": {"crossref": [{"title": "Multi-Kernel Convolutional Neural Network-Transformer for Early Warning of Upset Events in Industrial Furnaces", "doi": "10.2139/ssrn.5316635", "DOI": "10.2139/ssrn.5316635", "